Rakuen's dispatch registrar has been compiling a survey of Cinderteeth Mountains entry zone creatures for the Ventspeaker refugee community, who need current behavioral data for the volcanic wildlife they will encounter on any return route assessment. Blackstep basalt sentinels patrol the volcanic ridge zone, vent-crab swarms occupy the thermal spring approaches, and cinderpine resin-hawks nest in the foothills Pine Copse. Engage one of each and return behavioral data that the community's route planners can use for safety briefings.
The entry zone volcanic creature survey is complete and Rakuen's dispatch registrar has shared your behavioral data with the Ventspeaker refugee community's route planning committee. The committee notes with some relief that the blackstep basalt sentinels occupy fixed patrol routes that can be avoided with minor route adjustments, and the vent-crab swarm territories are mappable by thermal signature. The cinderpine resin-hawks remain unpredictable but the committee considers them a manageable hazard for prepared parties. The survey results are incorporated into the community's first formal return route safety briefing.
